               <p>JAMES EVANS. I am <rs id="t18280911-338-viclabel1737" type="occupation">in a gentleman's service</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-338-victim1837 t18280911-338-viclabel1737"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18280911-338-crimeloc1738">Chigwell, in Essex</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-338-crimeloc1738" type="placeName" value="Chigwell, in Essex"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-338-crimeloc1738" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-338-off1735 t18280911-338-crimeloc1738"></join> - I rent a room of Thomas Day; the prisoner lodged in the same house. On the 29th of July, I lost a watch from the mantel-piece - I had seen it safe half an hour before; we found the prisoner, who said he had pawned it in Bishopsgate-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-338-person1838">
                  THOMAS 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18280911-338-person1838" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-338-person1838" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-338-person1838" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came to me and said he was in very great distress; that he had a watch in pawn for 8s. - he asked me to buy it, and said I should have the duplicate for 2s.; I gave it him and got this watch, which I gave the officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-338-person1839">
                  GEORGE 
                  SEAWARD
               <interp inst="t18280911-338-person1839" type="surname" value="SEAWARD"></interp>
